Arissa Khan’s (@arissakhan) nikaah look by Rimple & Harpreet (@rimpleandharpreet) is bridal maximalism done right.
Rich embroidery, archival-inspired motifs, layered textures, and old-world opulence came together in a sharara that took over 16,800 hours to create.
Paired with custom jewellery by RAH Jewels (@therahjewels), the ensemble felt regal, cinematic, and a piece that could become a family heirloom.
For brides who want their nikaah wardrobe to feel grand, timeless, and unapologetically elaborate, this one deserves a spot on the moodboard.
